Package com.rb.nonbiz.json

Class JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.JavaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.json.JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
com.rb.nonbiz.json.JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.JavaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor
Enclosing class:
JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
public static class JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.JavaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor
extends JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
Tells us the type of property of a JsonObject in the JSON API, in the case where it is the JSON representation of a java generic such as Foo<T>.

It should only be used when T is an actual data class that has a JSON serialization. Example: UniqueId<NamedFactor>. It should not be used for 'marker interface' classes, such as Portfolio<HeldByUs>. This makes sense, because HeldByUs is not something that gets serialized.

For the inner classes, we use the more general JsonApiPropertyDescriptor instead of a raw Class. This allows us to support things like UniqueId<List<Double>>, i.e. situations where the generic argument class is not a 'simple' class. (This is an unrealistic example, as we'd never really need a unique ID of a list, but it should illustrate the point.)

    • javaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor

      public static JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.JavaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor javaGenericJsonApiPropertyDescriptor​(java.lang.Class<?> outerClass, JsonApiPropertyDescriptor first, JsonApiPropertyDescriptor... rest)
      Represents a property of an object that's a Java generic.

      Example: a NetGain<LongTerm>, where NetGain is the outer class, and LongTerm is the inner class (2nd argument).

      We normally use a builder when there can be two arguments of the same type, but this is meant to be used inline in the various definitions of JSON_VALIDATION_INSTRUCTIONS in the JSON API converter verb classes, so we want its invocation to look short.

    • getPropertySpecificDocumentation

      public java.util.Optional<JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation> getPropertySpecificDocumentation()
      Description copied from class: JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
      Per JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation documentation, it's used for cases where we want to attach context-specific documentation to a specific property of an object, vs. to the class.

      There are several cases where JsonApiPropertyDescriptors are nested. Example: a JsonApiPropertyDescriptor.CollectionJsonApiPropertyDescriptor of some other JsonApiPropertyDescriptor; e.g. a List of ClosedRange. Ideally, any extra JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation would only appear at the top level of this nesting (here, the List, and we shouldn't even be able to have more such JsonPropertySpecificDocumentation for the JsonApiPropertyDescriptors below (here, the ClosedRange). We will have preconditions for that, but we can't enforce it at runtime.

      Specified by:
      getPropertySpecificDocumentation in class JsonApiPropertyDescriptor
